                            <comment id="13009684" author="tdunning" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2011 15:51:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks fine.  It uses the less accurate formula for standard deviation, but that isn&apos;t a big deal in most applications.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To do better would require adapting Welford&apos;s method which would require some thought (which this implementation does not).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is also the question of progressively accumulating error.  Again, I don&apos;t think that the applications of this version&lt;br/&gt;
require that be addressed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
